_refine.details                                  
;THE MODEL CONTAINS FIVE RESIDUES OUT OF 1122 THAT FALL IN
THE GENEROUSLY ALLOWED REGION OF A RAMACHANDRAN PLOT AS
DEFINED IN PROCHECK AND ONE RESIDUE IN THE DISALLOWED
REGION.  TWO OF THE FIVE ARE ACTIVE SITE RESIDUES IN CHAIN
A AND B AND THE OTHER FOUR ARE INVOLVED IN
CRYSTALLOGRAPHIC CONTACTS.  THE RESIDUES ARE ARG A 216,
SER A 116, ASN A 461, SER B 116, AND ASN B 461.
;
